title.narrative: Convening of Commonwealth Health Ministers and Senior Officials

description.narrative:
The Commonwealth Health Ministers Meetings and the related meetings of the Commonwealth ministerial and senior officials’ meetings provide a unique opportunity for member states to share and learn from each other, forge common goals and work together to achieve consensus on policy positions and collaborative actions. The outcomes of these meetings are ministerial statements on agreements reached and future actions to be taken. The convening of the ministerial meetings and meetings of senior officials (through the Commonwealth Advisory Committee on Health), dissemination of ministerial outcomes and follow up of agreed actions, require Secretariat support and form the core of this project.
Note: The implementation of the Health Ministerial Meetings falls under the Consensus Building project of the delivery plan and Strategic Plan. Pillar 3.3. (Intermediate Outcome) relates to project work requested by Ministers at their annual meetings, ranging from research, proposals for Commonwealth collaborative platforms, to technical support. They focus on areas identified by member countries and regional bodies as areas of comparative advantage for the Secretariat.
